    "description": "<i>Time, Dr. Freeman? Is it really that time again?</i><br><br>Half-Life 2: VR Mod - Episode One is a community-made adaptation of Valve's episodic continuation of Half-Life 2, transformed into a fully roomscale Virtual Reality experience.<br><br>Return as Gordon Freeman to City 17 and deal with the consequences of your actions. Operate the gravity gun to deadly effect, battle gunships and striders and survive the darkness. Can you manage to escape City 17 with Alyx?<br><br><strong>Features:</strong><br><ul class=\"bb_ul\"><li> The same full room-scale VR experience you already know and love from the <i>Half-Life 2: VR Mod</i>, now available for Episode One!<br></li><li> Intuitive and realistic weapon interactions, with quick and easy weapon switching via a radial menu, ammo storage over your shoulder, functional iron-sights, two-handed weapons, and manual reloading. Optional laser sight and an arcade style &quot;quick reload&quot; are available if desired.<br></li><li> Increase your level of immersion with newly added support for bHaptics vests.<br></li><li> Playable on any VR headset which is supported by SteamVR.<br></li><li>Optional support for bHaptics vests and ProVolver haptic pistols</li></ul><br>Half-Life 2: VR Mod - Episode One is a community-developed modification and was not created by Valve Software.",
